Mongodb is non-SQL DB.
It take input in JSON format and store data into BISON format (Binary form of JSON)
It is vertical scalable.

    Mongodb                             SQL
DB-->Collection-->documents     DB-->Table-->row/column

_id :
    All documents mush have an _id field. If no _id is specified when a document is inserted, MongoDB will add the _id field as an ObjectId.
    _id is immutable
    Itcan not be an array
    the _id field must be unique to a collection
    It act as primary key for replication.
    Its a 12 byte Hex String ( Date | MAC | address | PID | Counter ) i.e. ObjectId("58dc309ce3f39998099d6275")

default port
-------------
mongos 27017
mongo-shard 27018
mongo-config 27019